WEBVTT

00:02.102 --> 00:03.536
<i>[jazzy music]</i>

00:03.602 --> 00:05.071
<i>- ♪ Timmy's</i>
<i>still an average kid ♪</i>

00:05.138 --> 00:07.340
<i>♪ That no one understands ♪</i>

00:07.407 --> 00:09.442
<i>♪ Chloe's his new neighbor ♪</i>

00:09.509 --> 00:11.878
<i>♪ And she's ruining</i>
<i>all his plans ♪</i>

00:11.945 --> 00:12.912
- Aah!

00:12.979 --> 00:13.913
<i>- ♪ All the wishes ♪</i>

00:13.980 --> 00:15.081
<i>♪ In the world ♪</i>

00:15.148 --> 00:17.250
<i>♪ So why should he care? ♪</i>

00:17.317 --> 00:19.552
<i>♪ Jorgen has reported</i>
<i>there's a fairy shortage ♪</i>

00:19.619 --> 00:21.755
<i>♪ So Timmy has to share ♪</i>

00:21.821 --> 00:24.758
<i>♪ His OddParents,</i>
<i>fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:24.824 --> 00:27.260
- More than one?
- This should be fun!

00:27.327 --> 00:29.229
<i>- ♪ OddParents,</i>
<i>fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:29.295 --> 00:32.232
<i>♪ Feather suit, nature boots,</i>
<i>laser shooting, rescue ♪</i>

00:32.298 --> 00:33.466
- World peace, kale treats,

00:33.533 --> 00:34.667
bunny feet, real neat!

00:34.734 --> 00:35.802
- What? No!
Leave me alone!

00:35.869 --> 00:38.438
My fairies!
Get your own!

00:38.505 --> 00:40.807
-<i> ♪ OddParents,</i>
<i>fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:40.874 --> 00:42.776
<i>♪ Timmy, beware,</i>
<i>you'll have to share ♪</i>

00:42.842 --> 00:44.711
{\an8}<i>♪ Your fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:44.778 --> 00:45.745
{\an8}- Yeah, right!

00:49.883 --> 00:52.819
{\an8}<i>[upbeat music]</i>

00:52.886 --> 00:59.259
{\an8}♪ ♪

00:59.325 --> 01:01.728
[bell ringing]

01:01.795 --> 01:04.563
[all cheering]

01:04.631 --> 01:05.732
- School's out!

01:05.799 --> 01:07.834
The nightmare's over.

01:07.901 --> 01:09.569
- I'm never going back.

01:09.636 --> 01:11.838
Tell my story!

01:11.905 --> 01:13.373
- Boy, this was a hectic day.

01:13.440 --> 01:15.408
{\an3}I taught the kindergartners
Mandarin Chinese

01:15.475 --> 01:17.277
{\an3}and created
an experimental cure

01:17.343 --> 01:19.012
for male-pattern baldness.

01:19.078 --> 01:20.513
- You think you
accomplished a lot?

01:20.580 --> 01:22.015
I found a new app that shows me

01:22.081 --> 01:23.950
what I look like with a beard.

01:24.017 --> 01:24.951
Check it.

01:25.018 --> 01:25.952
[beeping]

01:26.019 --> 01:28.054
Ladies, get in line.

01:28.121 --> 01:29.756
- Hey, Timmy and Chloe.

01:29.823 --> 01:31.157
Check out this new app.

01:31.224 --> 01:33.660
This is what Wanda looks like
with a beard.

01:33.726 --> 01:35.595
- Gentlemen, get in line.

01:35.662 --> 01:38.198
- Ooh, I know the perfect way
to relax after a day

01:38.264 --> 01:39.499
of super achieving.

01:39.566 --> 01:41.134
You guys are gonna love it.

01:41.201 --> 01:43.002
Cosmo and Wanda,
poof us to my house.

01:43.069 --> 01:44.370
<i>- Chloe!</i>

01:44.437 --> 01:46.239
Thanks to your experimental
baldness cure,

01:46.306 --> 01:47.307
I have hair.

01:47.373 --> 01:48.842
And, oddly,
webbed feet,

01:48.908 --> 01:50.376
but I'm okay with that!

01:50.443 --> 01:53.580
[magic wands chiming]

01:55.048 --> 01:56.249
- Let's start the fun

01:56.316 --> 01:58.518
with some healthy snacks.

02:00.286 --> 02:01.221
- [munching]

02:01.287 --> 02:02.222
[alarm buzzes]

02:02.288 --> 02:03.790
[retches]

02:03.857 --> 02:06.359
Something terrible's
happening in my mouth.

02:06.426 --> 02:08.026
This is not a cookie.

02:08.094 --> 02:09.027
- It's better.

02:09.095 --> 02:10.263
It's a tofookie,

02:10.330 --> 02:11.531
a cookie-like disk
made with tofu

02:11.598 --> 02:13.433
{\an8}and something called
cricket protein.

02:13.500 --> 02:14.367
- Why?

02:14.434 --> 02:16.603
- Now let's bump up the fun.

02:16.669 --> 02:19.205
{\an3}We're gonna watch
the greatest television show

02:19.272 --> 02:20.607
{\an3}ever made.

02:20.673 --> 02:23.176
<i>[triumphant music]</i>
<i>"The Fair Bears"!</i>

02:23.243 --> 02:24.811
- That show is the worst.

02:24.878 --> 02:27.480
I thought it was canceled.
Why wasn't it canceled?

02:27.547 --> 02:30.750
- It was, but I have all
26 seasons on DVD.

02:30.817 --> 02:33.119
Never touch them!

02:33.186 --> 02:35.755
[giggles]

02:35.822 --> 02:38.157
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

02:38.224 --> 02:40.860
<i>all: ♪ Welcome to a world</i>
<i>that's always fair ♪</i>

02:40.927 --> 02:43.530
<i>♪ Get wots of wuv from</i>
<i>friendly bears who care ♪</i>

02:43.596 --> 02:44.998
<i>♪ Be happy, be fair ♪</i>

02:45.064 --> 02:46.733
<i>♪ Be truthful ♪</i>
And share!

02:46.799 --> 02:48.535
<i>♪ We're the Fair Bears,</i>
<i>and we're fair ♪</i>

02:48.601 --> 02:50.436
- Stop telling me what to do,
Fair Bears.

02:50.503 --> 02:51.971
<i>- ♪ So if you're stressed</i>
<i>or feeling blue ♪</i>

02:52.038 --> 02:54.340
<i>♪ Come play with us</i>
<i>the whole day through ♪</i>

02:54.407 --> 02:55.909
<i>♪ We're ready for fun ♪</i>

02:55.975 --> 02:57.710
<i>♪ So how 'bout you? ♪</i>

02:57.777 --> 03:01.681
<i>all: ♪ We're the Fair Bears,</i>
<i>and we're fair ♪</i>

03:03.483 --> 03:05.919
{\an3}- Ooh, I love watching
"The Fair Bears."

03:05.985 --> 03:08.855
This is how I relax!

03:08.922 --> 03:11.057
- I don't want to
hurt Chloe's feelings,

03:11.124 --> 03:13.026
but those Fair Bears
make me want to

03:13.092 --> 03:15.295
cough up my tofookie.

03:15.361 --> 03:17.630
Know what I mean, Sport?

03:17.697 --> 03:20.633
{\an3}Sport?

03:20.700 --> 03:22.335
<i>Oh, I don't think so.</i>

03:22.402 --> 03:24.237
[magic wand chimes]

03:24.304 --> 03:25.939
{\an3}- Busted.

03:26.005 --> 03:27.340
<i>- I'm Fair Bear,</i>

03:27.407 --> 03:28.841
<i>and I never cheat.</i>

03:28.908 --> 03:32.178
{\an3}- Me neither,
'cause it's wrong.

03:32.245 --> 03:33.846
<i>- I'm Better Bear,</i>

03:33.913 --> 03:37.283
<i>and I believe that</i>
<i>no matter how good you are,</i>

03:37.350 --> 03:39.552
<i>you can</i>
<i>always be better.</i>

03:39.619 --> 03:41.287
- That's what I tell everybody.

03:41.354 --> 03:42.288
- What's with you?

03:42.355 --> 03:43.756
<i>- And I'm Happy Ray.</i>

03:43.823 --> 03:44.691
<i>Be happy.</i>

03:44.757 --> 03:47.060
<i>And that's an order.</i>

03:47.126 --> 03:48.328
- Sir, yes, sir.

03:48.394 --> 03:49.629
- I love the Fair Bears,

03:49.696 --> 03:51.130
but I'm not gonna lie, guys.

03:51.197 --> 03:53.766
Happy Ray scares me
a little.

03:53.833 --> 03:54.767
Guys?

03:56.970 --> 03:57.904
{\an1}- Busted.

03:57.971 --> 03:59.572
[magic wand chimes]

03:59.639 --> 04:02.875
- Ooh, I love the Fair Bears
so much.

04:02.942 --> 04:04.310
I wish they were real.

04:04.377 --> 04:06.212
Oh, oh, oh!

04:06.279 --> 04:07.280
I have fairies.

04:07.347 --> 04:08.581
They can be real.

04:08.648 --> 04:12.251
I wish the Fair Bears
were real!

04:12.318 --> 04:14.020
[magic wand chimes]
both: No!

04:14.087 --> 04:17.223
<i>[triumphant music]</i>

04:17.290 --> 04:19.192
- [gasps]

04:19.257 --> 04:20.192
[cheers and claps]

04:20.259 --> 04:21.628
- Look, bear buddies.

04:21.694 --> 04:24.597
We're in a super fun new world.

04:24.664 --> 04:26.499
- I'm Chloe,
and I brought you here

04:26.566 --> 04:27.900
because I love you.

04:27.967 --> 04:30.169
I love you so much.

04:30.236 --> 04:31.371
- I'm Cosmo.

04:31.437 --> 04:32.805
Want to see Wanda
with a beard?

04:32.872 --> 04:35.241
Sorry, I get flustered
around celebrities.

04:35.308 --> 04:36.376
- I'm Timmy,
and I'm leaving.

04:36.442 --> 04:37.744
{\an3}- Wait.

04:37.810 --> 04:40.113
What's that expression
on your face?

04:40.179 --> 04:43.983
It's like a smile,
but it's upside down.

04:44.050 --> 04:45.485
{\an8}- Can you sign my DVDs?

04:45.551 --> 04:46.719
{\an8}Use the glitter pen.

04:46.786 --> 04:47.520
{\an7}Use it!

04:47.587 --> 04:49.656
all: We all wuv you,

04:49.722 --> 04:53.292
and we want to be
your bear buddies.

04:53.359 --> 04:54.894
- Oh, you want to be my buddy?

04:54.961 --> 04:56.229
Quit touching my face!

04:56.295 --> 04:59.065
Right, Wanda?

04:59.132 --> 05:00.533
Get back here, woman!

05:01.734 --> 05:02.702
- [groans]

05:02.769 --> 05:05.538
{\an1}- Um, time for some
Fair Bear fun.

05:05.605 --> 05:08.408
Let's play the Fair Bear
board game.

05:08.474 --> 05:10.610
[all cheering]
- Huzzah!

05:10.677 --> 05:12.912
♪ ♪

05:12.979 --> 05:14.447
- I'm already bored.

05:14.514 --> 05:16.616
{\an1}- Don't worry;
I have a genius plan.

05:16.683 --> 05:18.918
- Hey, Timmy, you can go first.

05:18.985 --> 05:20.486
Roll the Nice Dice.

05:22.922 --> 05:24.057
- I rolled two.

05:24.123 --> 05:25.258
{\an1}One...

05:25.324 --> 05:26.259
Two. I win!

05:26.325 --> 05:27.960
{\an1}Game over.
Genius!

05:28.027 --> 05:29.796
We're out of here, Wanda.

05:29.862 --> 05:32.131
{\an3}- What was that
you just did?

05:32.198 --> 05:33.332
- It's called cheating.

05:33.399 --> 05:34.600
Timmy's an expert.

05:34.667 --> 05:37.003
- But it's not f--

05:37.070 --> 05:39.005
it's--it's not fair.

05:39.072 --> 05:41.140
- I have a funny feeling inside,

05:41.207 --> 05:42.141
and it's not--

05:42.208 --> 05:43.609
{\an1}[stammering]
happy.

05:43.676 --> 05:45.244
- Did you eat a tofookie?

05:45.311 --> 05:47.080
{\an1}'Cause those things
will turn on ya.

05:47.146 --> 05:49.182
- [whispering]
I'm bear-y uncomfortable.

05:49.248 --> 05:50.750
Someone make it better.

05:50.817 --> 05:54.287
{\an1}- Okay, let's all just take
a bear-y big breath

05:54.353 --> 05:56.889
{\an1}and sing the song
that helps us say bye-bye

05:56.956 --> 05:58.191
to bad feelings.

05:58.257 --> 06:00.927
all: "The Forgiveness Song"!

06:00.993 --> 06:02.695
<i>[upbeat piano music]</i>

06:02.762 --> 06:05.498
<i>all: ♪ You've got to forgive</i>
<i>and forget ♪</i>

06:05.565 --> 06:07.500
<i>♪ You can't live</i>
<i>with regret ♪</i>

06:07.567 --> 06:08.701
<i>♪ Whether you're</i>
<i>bear buddies ♪</i>

06:08.768 --> 06:10.436
<i>♪ Or you just met ♪</i>

06:10.503 --> 06:13.239
<i>♪ You got to forgive</i>
<i>and forget ♪</i>

06:13.306 --> 06:14.407
- Stop it!

06:14.474 --> 06:16.776
{\an1}- Timmy, this may sound
kind of harsh,

06:16.843 --> 06:18.811
{\an1}but you're being a little bit
of a bummer bear.

06:18.878 --> 06:20.513
{\an3}- Why does everything
you say now

06:20.580 --> 06:22.782
{\an3}have to have
the word "bear" in it?

06:22.849 --> 06:25.718
- Well, someone's a cranky bear.

06:25.785 --> 06:29.255
{\an1}- I know what makes cranky bears
feel better:

06:29.322 --> 06:30.890
{\an1}nap time!

06:30.957 --> 06:33.559
- Right, like I'm gonna
take a nap.

06:33.626 --> 06:35.261
I'm almost a tween.

06:35.328 --> 06:36.729
<i>[dreamy music]</i>

06:36.796 --> 06:38.197
<i>all bears:</i>
<i>♪ Put your sleepy head ♪</i>

06:38.264 --> 06:39.632
<i>♪ On your sleepy bed ♪</i>

06:39.699 --> 06:43.636
<i>♪ And close your eyes</i>
<i>and sleep ♪</i>

06:44.937 --> 06:47.373
- [snoring]

06:47.440 --> 06:49.342
[yawns]

06:49.408 --> 06:50.877
[unicorn whinnies]

06:50.943 --> 06:52.178
Where are we?

06:52.245 --> 06:54.447
This place looks like
a unicorn ate a rainbow

06:54.514 --> 06:55.448
and threw it up.

06:55.515 --> 06:57.350
- Or maybe it ate a tofookie.

06:57.416 --> 06:58.985
- We're in Happy Hollow,

06:59.051 --> 07:02.555
where cranky bears
come to wear the Happy Hat.

07:04.223 --> 07:05.758
- Listen up, bonker bears,

07:05.825 --> 07:08.628
{\an1}there's absolutely no way
that Wanda and I

07:08.694 --> 07:10.163
are putting on these--

07:10.229 --> 07:11.631
{\an3}- Do it!

07:12.565 --> 07:14.033
[shouting, hats zapping]

07:14.100 --> 07:15.034
[bell dings]

07:16.102 --> 07:17.036
[bell dings]

07:17.103 --> 07:18.805
[shimmering chimes]

07:20.206 --> 07:22.942
[all laughing]

07:23.009 --> 07:24.076
- Am I dreaming,

07:24.143 --> 07:25.878
{\an1}or are you guys
actually getting along?

07:25.945 --> 07:28.948
- We're bear-y, bear-y
good buddies now.

07:29.015 --> 07:30.983
- I wuv everyone.

07:31.050 --> 07:32.518
- We wore the Happy Hats

07:32.585 --> 07:34.520
with wires and blinking lights.

07:34.587 --> 07:36.088
I smelled smoke.

07:36.155 --> 07:38.691
- Wait, I've seen
every "Fair Bears" episode,

07:38.758 --> 07:39.926
like, a bazillion times,

07:39.992 --> 07:42.628
and I have never seen
a Happy Hat.

07:42.695 --> 07:44.430
- Who wants a hug?

07:44.497 --> 07:46.465
{\an1}- I do.
I wuv hugs!

07:46.532 --> 07:49.302
The nice bears changed my brain.

07:49.368 --> 07:51.571
- I'm not sure I'm wuv-ing this.

07:51.637 --> 07:53.873
You brainwashed my friends!

07:53.940 --> 07:55.308
I can't believe I'm saying this,

07:55.374 --> 07:58.444
but put Timmy's brain
back the way it was.

07:58.511 --> 08:01.214
{\an3}- We just made him
a better bear.

08:04.050 --> 08:05.218
- Boundaries, Timmy.

08:05.284 --> 08:06.586
You're creeping me out.

08:06.652 --> 08:07.954
- This is not cool.

08:08.020 --> 08:10.022
Turn my friends back
to the way they were.

08:10.089 --> 08:13.826
- Hey, Chloe, your smile turned
upside down.

08:13.893 --> 08:16.095
Maybe you should wear
the Happy Hat too.

08:16.162 --> 08:17.263
{\an3}- [screams]

08:17.330 --> 08:19.432
{\an3}The Fair Bears
are bonkers, Cosmo.

08:19.498 --> 08:20.633
Poof them away!

08:20.700 --> 08:22.668
<i>[triumphant music]</i>

08:22.735 --> 08:24.804
{\an1}- Sorry, I ate my wand
in my sleep.

08:24.871 --> 08:26.405
I thought it was a tofookie.

08:26.472 --> 08:28.407
all: Get 'em!

08:28.474 --> 08:29.575
- Run!

08:29.642 --> 08:31.010
- Don't worry,

08:31.077 --> 08:33.346
{\an1}I hid a super secret spare wand
in Timmy's room.

08:33.412 --> 08:34.513
It should be easy to find,

08:34.580 --> 08:36.448
because there are signs
all over town

08:36.515 --> 08:38.150
pointing to where it is.

08:38.217 --> 08:41.554
<i>[exciting music]</i>

08:41.621 --> 08:44.423
- Hunt them down!

08:44.490 --> 08:45.625
[tires screech]

08:47.059 --> 08:48.361
- I wuv you!

08:48.427 --> 08:49.528
♪ ♪

08:49.595 --> 08:50.663
{\an3}- Hey.

08:50.730 --> 08:52.899
both: Let's sing
the safety song!

08:52.965 --> 08:54.433
<i>all: ♪ When you cross</i>
<i>the street ♪</i>

08:54.500 --> 08:55.902
<i>♪ Always look both ways ♪</i>

08:55.968 --> 08:57.303
<i>♪ Da, da, da, da,</i>
<i>da, da, da, da ♪</i>

08:57.370 --> 08:58.804
<i>[scatting]</i>

08:58.871 --> 09:00.006
[car horn blaring]

09:00.072 --> 09:02.708
[crashing]

09:02.775 --> 09:04.577
{\an1}- Mother, I told you
not to drive

09:04.644 --> 09:06.112
right after your eye exam.

09:06.178 --> 09:08.614
{\an1}You want to go to prison again?
Is that what you want?

09:08.681 --> 09:10.850
- Denzel, is that you?

09:10.917 --> 09:12.985
<i>[alarm blaring]</i>
- My Fairy Finder's in a frenzy!

09:13.052 --> 09:14.820
I'm gonna bag me some fairies.

09:14.887 --> 09:16.455
You get the car to the chop shop

09:16.522 --> 09:18.457
{\an1}before the po-pos take you
to the pokey.

09:18.524 --> 09:21.961
♪ ♪

09:22.028 --> 09:24.497
[both groaning]

09:24.563 --> 09:28.367
{\an3}<i>both: ♪ Welcome to a world</i>
<i>that's always fair ♪</i>

09:28.434 --> 09:29.869
<i>♪ Get wots of wuv ♪</i>

09:29.936 --> 09:32.638
<i>♪ From friendly bears</i>
<i>who care ♪</i>

09:32.705 --> 09:34.006
[both groan]

09:34.073 --> 09:35.474
- I never thought I'd say this,

09:35.541 --> 09:37.910
{\an1}but that song
is driving me cuckoo!

09:37.977 --> 09:39.145
{\an3}- Relax.

09:39.211 --> 09:40.546
{\an3}All I have to do is follow
these signs

09:40.613 --> 09:41.914
to the spare wand.

09:41.981 --> 09:46.419
♪ ♪

09:46.485 --> 09:47.653
Hey.

09:47.720 --> 09:48.821
Ha!
What do you know?

09:48.888 --> 09:50.957
It was in my sock
the whole time.

09:51.023 --> 09:53.326
{\an1}Never would have found it
without the signs.

09:53.392 --> 09:54.961
[groans]

09:55.027 --> 09:57.997
{\an1}- You've been a bear-y bad bear,
Chloe!

09:58.064 --> 09:59.966
- You call yourselves
the Fair Bears,

10:00.032 --> 10:02.034
but there's nothing fair
about forcing people

10:02.101 --> 10:03.502
to be like you!

10:03.569 --> 10:06.472
You're the ones that have been
bear-y bad bears!

10:06.539 --> 10:08.107
Bad, bad bears!

10:08.174 --> 10:10.643
- You know, I've had
just about enough sass

10:10.710 --> 10:12.244
from you, Miss Thang!

10:14.013 --> 10:16.349
- Cosmo saves the day!

10:16.415 --> 10:18.384
{\an3}[groans]

10:18.451 --> 10:20.853
- My fairy finder found fairies!

10:20.920 --> 10:22.521
Fork 'em over, folks.

10:22.588 --> 10:23.689
- Fairies? Here?

10:23.756 --> 10:24.991
{\an3}No.
[laughs]

10:25.057 --> 10:27.493
Oh, wait--yes, yes,
there are fairies,

10:27.560 --> 10:29.228
and they're right there.

10:29.295 --> 10:30.863
all: Wait, what?

10:30.930 --> 10:31.964
- They're not fairies.

10:32.031 --> 10:33.666
They're Fair Bears,

10:33.733 --> 10:35.368
and I wuv them.

10:35.434 --> 10:37.370
- Ooh, let's see,
who should I believe?

10:37.436 --> 10:38.704
The boy who always lies

10:38.771 --> 10:40.373
or the girl
who always tells the truth?

10:40.439 --> 10:41.374
Tough call.

10:41.440 --> 10:42.708
Fairies in the hole!

10:42.775 --> 10:44.510
[vacuum whirring]

10:44.577 --> 10:48.247
all: No fair!

10:52.218 --> 10:54.820
If the po-pos ask,
I was never here.

10:54.887 --> 10:56.355
[both groaning]

10:56.422 --> 10:58.090
♪ ♪

10:58.157 --> 11:00.760
- I wish Wanda and Timmy
were back to normal.

11:00.826 --> 11:03.696
Hurry, before Timmy
hugs me again!

11:03.763 --> 11:09.835
♪ ♪

11:09.902 --> 11:12.138
- Ew, girl cooties.

11:12.204 --> 11:14.006
- What happened
to the Fair Bears?

11:14.073 --> 11:15.574
Nothing good, I hope.

11:15.641 --> 11:17.643
- Oh, don't worry.

11:17.710 --> 11:20.880
I can pretty much
guarantee that.

11:20.946 --> 11:23.282
[vacuum whirs]

11:23.349 --> 11:26.552
{\an3}- At last, my lifelong dream
of having fairies

11:26.619 --> 11:27.887
has come true.

11:27.953 --> 11:30.523
For my first wish--
ooh, so excited!

11:30.589 --> 11:31.524
I want you to, uh...

11:31.590 --> 11:33.859
<i>- Denzel, is that you?</i>

11:33.926 --> 11:35.494
[all screaming]

11:35.561 --> 11:36.629
[crashing]

11:36.695 --> 11:39.565
- [screams]
Why, Mother?

11:39.632 --> 11:41.634
- That wasn't bear-y fair.

11:41.700 --> 11:43.202
- I could be better.

11:43.269 --> 11:46.205
- Let's sing the revenge song.

11:46.272 --> 11:48.374
♪ ♪

11:52.611 --> 11:55.748
{\an8}<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

11:55.815 --> 12:01.320
{\an8}♪ ♪

12:02.455 --> 12:03.389
<i>- [yawns]</i>

12:03.456 --> 12:04.890
Another awesome day

12:04.957 --> 12:08.194
where my fairies do
absolutely everything for me.

12:08.260 --> 12:09.428
Cosmo, Wanda.

12:09.495 --> 12:10.830
Open my eyes.

12:10.896 --> 12:12.331
{\an8}[magic wands chime]

12:13.966 --> 12:15.034
Now dress me, please.

12:15.101 --> 12:16.802
[magic wand chimes]

12:18.838 --> 12:20.039
{\an1}- Done.
You're in a dress.

12:20.106 --> 12:21.307
You go, girl.

12:21.373 --> 12:24.410
- Oh, dear,
I can't un-see that.

12:27.580 --> 12:28.948
Well, bye, Sport.

12:29.014 --> 12:31.517
We're off to the Fairy World
iWand store

12:31.584 --> 12:33.486
to line up
for the new iWand.

12:33.552 --> 12:35.488
- We're getting
awesome upgrades:

12:35.554 --> 12:37.990
Wish Autocorrect,
faster Wand-Fi,

12:38.057 --> 12:39.492
and a Find-Your-Wand app,

12:39.558 --> 12:41.894
which I need,
'cause I lost my wand.

12:41.961 --> 12:43.162
- It's in your hand!

12:43.229 --> 12:45.397
{\an3}- Now, see, if I had
the Find-Your-Wand app,

12:45.464 --> 12:46.532
I would have known that.

12:46.599 --> 12:47.600
- You can't go.

12:47.666 --> 12:48.701
In case you haven't noticed,

12:48.767 --> 12:50.302
I'm not great on my own.

12:50.369 --> 12:52.304
My eyes are dry.
Blink for me.

12:52.371 --> 12:53.506
- Don't worry, Sport.

12:53.572 --> 12:55.040
{\an3}We asked Chloe
to look after you

12:55.107 --> 12:56.509
while we're gone.

12:56.575 --> 12:58.310
- Yeah, we know you're basically

12:58.377 --> 12:59.879
a potato with a hat.

12:59.945 --> 13:03.149
{\an1}- Chloe Carmichael,
reporting for babysitting duty.

13:03.215 --> 13:05.518
So where's the wittle cutie?

13:05.584 --> 13:07.953
- Wanda, raise my hand.

13:08.020 --> 13:09.989
[magic wand chimes]

13:10.055 --> 13:11.490
- I'm babysitting Timmy?

13:11.557 --> 13:14.059
- I'm not used to doing things
without my fairies.

13:14.126 --> 13:15.161
[yelps]

13:15.227 --> 13:16.262
- Don't worry, Timmy.

13:16.328 --> 13:18.731
{\an1}Wanda and Cosmo
will be back soon.

13:18.797 --> 13:19.632
{\an1}How soon?

13:19.698 --> 13:21.167
- We'll be back by dark.

13:21.233 --> 13:22.635
- I wish it was dark!

13:22.701 --> 13:23.969
- I'd grant that wish,

13:24.036 --> 13:25.304
but I lost my wand.

13:25.371 --> 13:26.539
- It's in your hand!

13:26.605 --> 13:28.807
You're a potato with a wand.

13:28.874 --> 13:29.675
- [yells]

13:29.742 --> 13:32.478
I'm helpless till dark.

13:32.545 --> 13:34.180
- Spending months
in this thorn bush

13:34.246 --> 13:35.381
finally paid off.

13:35.447 --> 13:36.882
[groans]

13:36.949 --> 13:39.852
My arch enemy, Timmy Turner,
is defenseless.

13:39.919 --> 13:44.089
Time to alert the League
of Super Evil Revenge Seekers.

13:44.156 --> 13:45.891
Ring, ring.

13:45.958 --> 13:47.259
<i>Ring, ring.</i>

13:47.326 --> 13:48.494
<i>Ring, ring.</i>

13:48.561 --> 13:49.828
- [barks]

13:49.895 --> 13:51.030
- [giggles]

13:51.096 --> 13:52.731
<i>- Ring, ring.</i>

13:52.798 --> 13:55.534
{\an3}- Hello? Flipsie Fan Club,
Dark Laser speaking.

13:55.601 --> 13:58.537
{\an1}- Dark Laser, Timmy Turner
is vulnerable till dark.

13:58.604 --> 14:00.439
- Ooh, I am so there,

14:00.506 --> 14:02.541
but first I have
to walk Flipsie.

14:02.608 --> 14:04.410
{\an1}- Flipsie doesn't walk;
it just flips.

14:04.476 --> 14:05.744
I hate Flipsie!

14:05.811 --> 14:07.179
{\an1}See you in five
at the Cake 'n Bacon.

14:07.246 --> 14:08.247
You're buying.

14:08.314 --> 14:09.248
{\an1}[screams]

14:09.315 --> 14:11.016
Thorns in bad places!

14:11.083 --> 14:13.219
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:13.285 --> 14:14.220
<i>Ring, ring.</i>

14:14.286 --> 14:15.254
- Hello?

14:15.321 --> 14:17.389
- Foop, it's Turner time.

14:17.456 --> 14:19.058
{\an1}- [giggles]
Goody.

14:19.124 --> 14:20.226
But I'll be a minute.

14:20.292 --> 14:21.827
{\an1}I'm in a time-out
for putting spiders

14:21.894 --> 14:23.329
in my daddy's pis-ghetti.

14:23.395 --> 14:25.331
- With my team
of borderline lunatics,

14:25.397 --> 14:26.832
I'm invincible!

14:26.899 --> 14:29.235
- Time to trim the talking bush.

14:29.301 --> 14:30.703
[string trimmer buzzes]

14:30.769 --> 14:32.571
{\an3}- [screams]
Not invincible!

14:32.638 --> 14:35.774
<i>The League of Super Evil</i>
<i>Revenge Seekers unite.</i>

14:35.841 --> 14:37.109
Who are we?

14:37.176 --> 14:38.844
{\an8}all: Losers!

14:38.911 --> 14:40.913
- Today's a momentous day.

14:40.980 --> 14:42.081
- You bet it is.

14:42.147 --> 14:44.083
It's Bottomless
Clam Chowder Day.

14:44.149 --> 14:46.685
{\an1}- That, and we're going
to annihilate a ten-year-old!

14:46.752 --> 14:48.087
- Just a heads-up,

14:48.153 --> 14:50.389
{\an3}I can only pay
with the teeth of my enemies.

14:50.456 --> 14:52.024
It's legal tender in space.

14:52.091 --> 14:53.892
{\an1}- Teeth back in the wallet,
nut job!

14:53.959 --> 14:56.195
{\an1}We need a plan
to destroy Turner.

14:56.262 --> 14:59.431
- Well, you know I have a thing
for poisonous spiders.

14:59.498 --> 15:00.466
Listen up.

15:00.532 --> 15:02.334
[whispering]

15:02.401 --> 15:05.871
[all laughing]

15:05.938 --> 15:08.073
- Ooh, you're one bad baby.

15:08.140 --> 15:09.041
{\an1}Me likey.

15:09.108 --> 15:10.576
- Flipsie has some questions.

15:10.643 --> 15:11.777
- [barks]

15:11.844 --> 15:14.480
{\an1}- Flipsie has a C-battery
for a brain!

15:14.546 --> 15:16.582
<i>- Did you dress yourself yet,</i>
<i>Timmy?</i>

15:16.649 --> 15:18.117
I know you can do it.

15:19.652 --> 15:20.619
- Nailed it.

15:20.686 --> 15:22.855
- Ooh, that's super close.

15:22.921 --> 15:25.391
Remember the song we practiced?

15:25.457 --> 15:27.493
♪ If you want to dress neat ♪

15:27.559 --> 15:29.361
{\an3}♪ You put your shoes
on your ♪

15:29.428 --> 15:31.096
- ♪ Hands ♪

15:31.163 --> 15:32.097
[doorbell rings]

15:34.667 --> 15:36.101
- Spider delivery.

15:36.168 --> 15:37.436
{\an3}- [groans]

15:37.503 --> 15:40.639
{\an3}You're not supposed
to say "spider."

15:40.706 --> 15:42.141
[doorbell rings]

15:42.207 --> 15:44.343
- Spider delivery.

15:44.410 --> 15:45.978
{\an3}- [groans]
Switch it up.

15:47.446 --> 15:49.782
- Uh...what's my line again?

15:51.016 --> 15:52.251
{\an1}- [groans]

15:52.318 --> 15:53.552
[doorbell rings]

15:53.619 --> 15:55.487
Pis-ghetti delivery.

15:55.554 --> 15:56.855
She's giving me a weird look.

15:56.922 --> 15:58.824
{\an3}I knew we should have
gone with pizza.

15:58.891 --> 16:00.025
Who orders pis-ghetti?

16:00.092 --> 16:01.093
[clears throat]

16:01.160 --> 16:03.796
Anyway, here's your pis-ghetti.

16:03.862 --> 16:06.031
{\an3}Don't open it
till we're far away.

16:06.098 --> 16:07.700
- Uh, thank you?

16:07.766 --> 16:10.969
{\an3}Wow.
Were they losers or what?

16:11.036 --> 16:12.938
- Yes, and they're
my sworn enemies.

16:13.005 --> 16:16.141
{\an1}Whatever's in that bag--
it isn't pis-ghetti.

16:16.208 --> 16:17.376
- Right you are.

16:17.443 --> 16:20.713
{\an3}It's just a bag
of deadly spiders.

16:20.779 --> 16:21.947
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

16:22.014 --> 16:22.948
[screams]

16:23.015 --> 16:23.749
Deadly spiders!

16:23.816 --> 16:24.950
[all laughing]

16:25.017 --> 16:26.218
{\an3}- Quiet!

16:26.285 --> 16:28.887
{\an3}Wait for the agonizing
screams of terror.

16:31.590 --> 16:34.727
[all screaming]

16:37.162 --> 16:40.833
<i>[whimsical music]</i>

16:40.899 --> 16:42.935
- I can't wait for my upgrade.

16:43.001 --> 16:45.838
Steve Wandzniak is a genius.

16:45.904 --> 16:47.673
Oh, it's him!

16:49.475 --> 16:51.577
- Good news, fellow fairy nerds.

16:51.643 --> 16:52.845
Well, for me, anyway.

16:52.911 --> 16:55.080
There's only two iWands left.

16:55.147 --> 16:58.050
You fight over them
while I make my escape.

17:00.219 --> 17:02.388
- Everyone, stay calm...

17:02.454 --> 17:04.757
{\an1}while we grab
the last two wands!

17:06.290 --> 17:09.494
[all yelling]

17:09.560 --> 17:10.561
<i>- Okay, champ.</i>

17:10.628 --> 17:12.030
Let's try walking.

17:12.097 --> 17:13.165
{\an1}It's easy.

17:13.232 --> 17:15.434
{\an1}Just put one foot
in front of the other.

17:15.501 --> 17:17.435
Left, right, left, right.

17:17.502 --> 17:19.405
- Got it.
Left, left, left.

17:19.471 --> 17:20.406
[yells]

17:20.472 --> 17:21.839
- Wow. Really?

17:21.906 --> 17:24.209
No right, just the
left and the left and the left?

17:24.276 --> 17:26.310
And I still have three hours
till dark.

17:26.377 --> 17:29.515
{\an1}- Oh, it's gonna get dark
a lot sooner than that,

17:29.581 --> 17:30.749
little missy.

17:30.816 --> 17:32.217
<i>- Quiet, she'll hear us!</i>

17:32.284 --> 17:33.285
[doorbell rings]

17:33.352 --> 17:34.420
{\an8}- Now watch how much better

17:34.486 --> 17:36.121
{\an8}this scam works with pizza.

17:36.188 --> 17:40.259
- "'Who is it?' she said,
already knowing who it was."

17:40.325 --> 17:41.627
- Spider delivery.

17:41.693 --> 17:44.129
{\an3}[groans]
Now you've got me saying it.

17:44.196 --> 17:46.732
- Ugh, I'm surrounded
by nincompoops!

17:46.799 --> 17:48.300
- Pizza delivery.

17:48.367 --> 17:50.502
{\an1}Nailed it!

17:50.569 --> 17:53.605
- You are getting very sleepy.

17:53.672 --> 17:54.807
[all snoring]

17:54.873 --> 17:57.309
- Oh, mother, mother.

17:57.376 --> 17:58.310
{\an3}[groans]

17:58.377 --> 17:59.645
- Man, I'm good.

17:59.711 --> 18:02.448
Then again...nincompoops!

18:02.514 --> 18:03.582
- [groans]

18:03.649 --> 18:07.286
- Time to wake up
the snoring bush!

18:07.352 --> 18:10.289
[all shouting]

18:11.457 --> 18:14.393
[all screaming]

18:16.395 --> 18:18.430
- Mother, we're making
a super evil plan,

18:18.497 --> 18:20.699
so we'll need snickerdoodles
and juice boxes.

18:20.766 --> 18:22.167
- You still live
with your mother?

18:22.234 --> 18:23.535
That's weird.

18:23.602 --> 18:26.271
Flipsie and I went
halfsies on a bachelor pad.

18:26.338 --> 18:28.240
Who's Daddy's little wingman?

18:28.307 --> 18:30.142
[giggles]

18:30.209 --> 18:32.244
- Goody, I found a spot
on my body

18:32.311 --> 18:33.979
where I wasn't bitten
by a spider.

18:34.046 --> 18:34.780
[groans]

18:34.847 --> 18:36.348
Never mind.

18:36.415 --> 18:38.784
{\an3}- We only have an hour
of daylight left to get Turner.

18:38.851 --> 18:40.586
Let's brainstorm a new plan.

18:40.652 --> 18:43.155
{\an1}- I know--
prank phone calls--

18:43.222 --> 18:45.991
{\an1}really mean ones
with cutting personal slights.

18:46.058 --> 18:47.926
- Or we just have him
move in with Mother.

18:47.993 --> 18:50.596
{\an3}No human can survive that
for long.

18:50.662 --> 18:52.064
Mother, snickerdoodles!

18:52.130 --> 18:54.700
- Well, we could use
my death annihilator ray,

18:54.766 --> 18:55.868
or--ooh!

18:55.934 --> 18:57.402
We could ding-dong-ditch
his house;

18:57.469 --> 18:59.605
you know, where you ring
the doorbell and run away.

18:59.671 --> 19:01.740
[giggles]

19:01.807 --> 19:03.642
- Whoa, tap the breaks.

19:03.709 --> 19:05.310
{\an3}You have
a death annihilator ray?

19:05.377 --> 19:08.080
{\an3}You couldn't have brought
that up before the pizza fiasco?

19:08.146 --> 19:10.883
- Losers, we finally have a plan

19:10.949 --> 19:13.452
to annihilate Timmy Turner.

19:13.519 --> 19:15.053
<i>- Snack-y time.</i>

19:16.522 --> 19:18.757
both: Hello, Mrs. Crocker.

19:18.824 --> 19:20.158
- Hello, boys.

19:20.225 --> 19:21.894
Here are your snickerdoodles.

19:21.960 --> 19:23.862
Now get back to your evil.

19:23.929 --> 19:26.031
- Killer doodles, Mrs. Crocker.

19:27.065 --> 19:29.468
- Hey, Laser, eyes up here.

19:30.836 --> 19:32.137
- Okay, buddy.

19:32.204 --> 19:34.840
{\an3}Which utensil
do we eat our soup with?

19:34.907 --> 19:36.308
This is an easy one.

19:39.511 --> 19:40.479
- [slurps]

19:40.546 --> 19:42.447
- You bozo.

19:42.514 --> 19:43.982
It's the spoon!

19:44.049 --> 19:46.752
What are you,
a single-cell organism?

19:46.818 --> 19:48.186
{\an3}Open wide.

19:48.253 --> 19:49.888
Here comes the choo-choo train.

19:49.955 --> 19:51.990
{\an3}Choo, choo.
Choo, choo.

19:52.057 --> 19:55.928
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:55.994 --> 19:57.563
- Pizza delivery.

19:57.629 --> 19:59.264
- We're not doing that anymore.

19:59.331 --> 20:00.265
[growls]

20:00.332 --> 20:01.300
[laser gun fires]

20:01.366 --> 20:02.668
[both screaming]

20:02.734 --> 20:04.736
{\an3}- Run!

20:04.803 --> 20:05.737
- Left, left, left!

20:05.804 --> 20:06.738
[yells]

20:06.805 --> 20:07.673
- Oh, brother.

20:07.739 --> 20:09.308
- [screaming]

20:09.374 --> 20:10.509
[laser gun fires]

20:10.576 --> 20:11.677
♪ ♪

20:11.743 --> 20:14.012
- [screams]

20:14.079 --> 20:16.882
{\an1}- So good to get out
of that chaos and get back

20:16.949 --> 20:19.718
to the peace and quiet of home.

20:19.785 --> 20:21.620
{\an1}Why's there a smoking hole
in the wall?

20:21.687 --> 20:23.055
- Could be anything.

20:23.121 --> 20:26.692
{\an3}Construction, big termites,
annihilator ray...

20:26.758 --> 20:28.193
[laser gun fires]

20:28.260 --> 20:29.628
[both screaming]

20:29.695 --> 20:32.531
{\an1}- The losers are after us,
and there was pizza with spiders

20:32.598 --> 20:34.066
{\an1}and left, left, left
is wrong!

20:34.132 --> 20:37.302
- He can't eat soup by himself!

20:37.369 --> 20:39.404
{\an1}- This may be a bad time
to bring this up,

20:39.471 --> 20:40.439
but is your mother...

20:40.505 --> 20:41.607
seeing anyone?

20:41.673 --> 20:43.742
- [screams]
What is wrong with you

20:43.809 --> 20:44.743
besides everything?

20:44.810 --> 20:46.345
- No worries, Timmy.

20:46.411 --> 20:49.114
We'll just poof them away
with our upgraded iWands.

20:49.181 --> 20:51.883
The software upload
should only take a minute,

20:51.950 --> 20:53.385
unless there's a glitch.

20:53.452 --> 20:55.420
[wand beeps]

20:55.487 --> 20:56.788
There's a glitch.

20:56.855 --> 20:58.557
- I'll call tech support.

20:58.624 --> 20:59.691
[laser gun firing]

20:59.758 --> 21:00.959
I'm on hold!

21:01.026 --> 21:02.527
- Okay, it's all good.

21:02.594 --> 21:03.729
I just need a password.

21:03.795 --> 21:05.063
Let's see.
"Cosmo"?

21:05.130 --> 21:06.765
No, I'll never remember that.

21:06.832 --> 21:07.733
- Just do it!

21:07.799 --> 21:09.034
- "Just do it."

21:09.101 --> 21:10.369
Ooh, fun password.

21:10.435 --> 21:11.903
{\an3}[wand beeps]
Oh, it's taken.

21:11.970 --> 21:14.573
Glitched again.

21:14.640 --> 21:17.776
- Your time on this Earth
is done, Timmy Turner.

21:17.843 --> 21:18.810
Did that sound scary?

21:18.877 --> 21:20.412
I--I--I wanted to sound scary.

21:20.479 --> 21:22.381
<i>[accordion music]</i>

21:22.447 --> 21:24.883
- Pizza delivery.

21:24.950 --> 21:27.819
- I'm feeling peckish.

21:27.886 --> 21:29.421
[all screaming]

21:29.488 --> 21:31.757
{\an3}- I can grant a wish
in ten seconds.

21:31.823 --> 21:33.525
{\an3}I'm just downloading
my pictures.

21:33.592 --> 21:34.526
Oh, look, Wanda.

21:34.593 --> 21:35.727
It's us at that luau.

21:35.794 --> 21:37.129
You look hot.

21:37.195 --> 21:39.364
{\an3}Seriously, you were sweating
like a pig.

21:39.431 --> 21:40.832
[laser gun fires]

21:40.899 --> 21:41.833
- [screams]

21:41.900 --> 21:43.035
[explosion]

21:43.101 --> 21:45.604
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

21:45.671 --> 21:46.605
[all screaming]

21:46.672 --> 21:48.073
[all cheering]

21:48.140 --> 21:49.474
- We annihilated Turner.

21:49.541 --> 21:50.475
We did it!

21:50.542 --> 21:51.843
Well, you did it.

21:51.910 --> 21:53.378
{\an3}That's my story,
and I'm sticking to it.

21:53.445 --> 21:56.314
- So that's our story?
We blame him?

21:56.381 --> 21:57.983
- Wait, what?
It wasn't me.

21:58.050 --> 22:00.252
It--it was Flipsie.
Sorry, Flipsie.

22:00.318 --> 22:02.988
Daddy's too pretty for jail.
[giggles]

22:03.055 --> 22:04.089
I'll call you, baby.

22:04.156 --> 22:06.625
[all yelling]

22:06.692 --> 22:07.793
- Oh, Timmy.

22:07.859 --> 22:09.928
{\an3}I'm sorry I called you
a bozo,

22:09.995 --> 22:11.697
but you kind of were
a little bit.

22:11.763 --> 22:13.365
- I will avenge you...

22:13.432 --> 22:16.134
right after I watch
